# scribe-dispatch watch timer environment (install to ~/.config/scribectl/watch.env).
# The unit reads only these; everything else is baked into the .service.

# REQUIRED — which project this timer watches. One project per timer: to watch
# a second, copy the unit to scribe-dispatch-watch@.service or a renamed unit
# with its own env file. A name with spaces is fine (the unit quotes it).
WATCH_PROJECT=Fertile Flames

# Vault root, only if you are not on the built-in /media/Creative default
# (the fixtures use this; a real single-vault install usually omits it):
# SCRIBECTL_VAULT=/media/Creative

# Per-machine dispatch routing (runner per skill, base_url for the local
# writer) lives in ~/.config/scribectl/dispatch.yaml, not here — the timer
# inherits it exactly as an interactive `scribe-dispatch` would.
